<br>
The game is PvP at its core, and it is the vision of the above quote that is causing this game to fail ATM.<br>
<br>
Take a look at Midgard Healers, for example.  Midgard is so dependent on Healers for success in RvR its not funny.<br>
<br>
Now, what happens when some changes come into the game that upset Healers and they start to leave?  The whole of Midgard suffers, that is what happens.<br>
<br>
If your class is dependent on class x and class y to be viable in RvR, then what happens when class x and class y don't play any more?<br>
<br>
Class interdependency is bad for a PvP game, period... and that is what this game is.  There is no real difference between RvR and PvP dynamics except that you are not allowed to attack everyone and anyone.  <br>
<br>
Every class should be able to bring something to the table in a one-on-one PvP situation.  Every single class.  Classes that can not function in one-on-one PvP are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> fun classes to play in the long run... and people eventually grow to realize this.  When they do, you have a very bad situation if other classes depended on that class for survival.<br>
<br>
<br>
edit:  Just read your post, Aiden.  You make some very good points there about the tradeoff with gameplay for PvE and PvP.  I agree with pretty much everything you said.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uraggoktp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaggokTP</A> at: 7/18/02 11:07:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaiden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aiden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/18/02 12:26:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3747.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: soooo is it safe to say we are a &quot;broken&quot; clas</span><hr size=1> you guys cant talk about content as is if it was the game.<br>
<br>
content is nothing more then the path a designer takes to continue the game. class balance,new content,new areas new things only prolong the life of the game.<br>
<br>
when you look at EQ vs UO vs AC vs Daoc you have to look at the core issues of what those games are trying to accomplish,and how well they do it.<br>
<br>
the same can be said for class balance,its not the basic issue when you look at the game. class balance is one of the last things you do,once you have the basic structure of the game set up. if your basic structure isnt there,you will never be able to achieve class balance,thus you wont accomplish what your trying to.<br>
<br>
